#include 'template.wml'

<table class="mydemo">
<tr class="mydemo">
<td class="mydemo">

<h3>Demo</h3>

<ol>

<li>
Open lena.png.
</li>

<li>
Select

<menupath>
&lt;Image&gt; -&gt; Filters -&gt; Generic -&gt; "Convolution Matrix..."
</menupath>

</li>

<li>
Set the 9 middle squares to 1, the other squares to 0 and the divisor to 9.<br />
(What we are doing is replacing every pixel with the average of its 3*3
neighbourhood.)
</li>

<li>
Press the "OK" button.
</li>

<li>
Repeat several times with Alt+F (or


<menupath>
&lt;Image&gt; -&gt; Filters -&gt; "Repeat Last"
</menupath>

) to strengthen the effect.
</li>

</ol>

</td>
</tr>
</table>
